first install helm in your server from official document

helm create myhelm
ll
cd myhelm
ll
# in templates you can modify the manifest files as per your requirements
# we can also use our own manifest files in the templates folder by deleting the default files
cd templates # in this folder create your own manifests files   deployment, HPA, Service, etc.
cd myhelm
helm install myrelease .
helm list
kubectl get all
helm uninstall myrelease
helm upgrade myrelease .      # if we modify any manifest files
helm history
helm rollback myrelease 1

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
how to host the helm chart publicly

helm lint myhelm 
helm package myhelm
ll
helm repo index .

install git in your server
yum install git -y
create empty repo in github and clone to the server myhelmrepo
git clone repo_url
mv myhelm-0.1.0.tgz  index.yaml  myhelmrepo
cd myhelmrepo
git add *
git commit -m "all" .
git push -u origin main

see the files github
go to settings --- pages--- main root and save --- you will get url
go to server
helm repo add myrelease (github_url)
helm repo list
helm install name myrelase/myhelm




























